<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870220-0160 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:The Cutting Edge</HL><DD> 02/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   Re James Perry's Feb. 3 page-one article on Venetian gondolas: The bow ornament, or &quot;ferro,&quot; was originally a blade mounted on the doge's gondola. The doge always had the right of way, and the blade was used to slice through the tow ropes of impertinent barge operators in his path.    Robert S. Holtzman   Newport, R.I.</TEXT></DOC>